## Article
- Title: Cross-site request forgery(CSRF) -MDN
- Link: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Attacks/CSRF
- Topic: Cross-site request forgery

## Summary in Japanese
- CSRFは，攻撃者がユーザーのブラウザを騙して，ユーザー本人の資格情報（セッションクッキー）付きで，勝手に状態変更リクエストを送らせる攻撃．
- 攻撃例は，POST を使う攻撃（form + submit）とGET を使う攻撃（img src）が存在する．

## English Summary
- CSRF is an attack in which an adversary tricks a user's browser into sending state‑changing requests on behalf of the user, accompanied by the user’s own credentials (session cookies).
  Attack techniques include POST‑based attacks using a form + submit() and GET‑based attacks using an img tag.

